Niger United, Kano Pillars, Police Machine, Safety Babes, Seasider Queens won their games in some of yesterday’s fixtures on Matchday Four of the Prudent Energy Handball Premier League Phase One holding at the Moshood Abiola National Stadium, Abuja. Former champion, Niger United beat Confluence Stars 37 to 28, while Benue Buffaloes lost 24 to 37 to Kano Pillars, just as Police Machine outmuscled Owena Kings 26 to 21 in the men’s category. In the women’s class, Safety Babes walloped Defender Babes 22 to 31, while Seasider Queens walked over Kada Queens, just as Imo Grasshoppers drew 37 to 37 with Rima Queens. In today’s matches, Imo Grasshoppers will battle with Seasider Babes, Defender Babes will take on Plateau Peacocks, while Kada Queens meet Safety Babes and Edo Dynamos take on Adorable Angels in the women’s games. The men’s fixtures will see Kada Stars clash with Benue Buffaloes, Police Machine take on Rima Strikers, Owena Kings duel with Tojemarine Academy, Confluence Stars against Safety Shooters, D:Defenders challenge Kano Pillars and Niger United meet Lagos Seasiders. 